default4.3
default 
defaultTh
defaultere are further concerns about accountability. In a recent article in Transport XTra, Professor Tony Travers of the London School of Economics
default wrote,
default “LEPs and local transport bodies are not local government. At the margin they are less legitimate than loc
defaultal government, pure and simple”.   
defaultFurther concerns come from the recent National Audit Office report which stated: 
default‘Locally, it is not clear that the government has achieved its objective to “increase democratic accountability and transparency, and ensu
defaultre that public expenditure is more responsive to the need
defaults of local business and people” ’
