defaultLocal Enterprise Partnerships are not subject to the same transparency requirements as local authorities
default’
default. Not only is it unclear whether LEPs have to abide by the same equality requirements as local authorities but 
defaultwe are concerned that it will be more difficult for disability groups, such as Guide Dogs, to monitor the work of LEPs and hold them to account. 
defaultDevolving responsibility for large amounts of transport funding to these bodies may 
defaultresult in less transparent and 
defaultless accountable decision 
defaultmaking, which will have a negative impact upon disabled people. 
